&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are supporting&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The NATO Support and Procurement Agency (NSPA) is a key agency within the North Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO) focused on providing comprehensive logistics, procurement, and support services to NATO member countries, partners, and other customers. The NSPA facilitates the collective acquisition and management of goods and services, ranging from military equipment to general supplies, enhancing the efficiency and effectiveness of NATO operations.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The agency&#39;s responsibilities include:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Procurement: managing the acquisition of a wide range of goods and services, including military equipment, supplies, and support services.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Logistics: offering logistics support such as transportation, warehousing, and distribution to ensure that NATO forces have the necessary resources when and where they are needed.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintenance: providing maintenance and repair services for military equipment, ensuring operational readiness and extending the lifespan of assets.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Project Management: overseeing and implementing various projects, including infrastructure development and other support activities.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The NSPA operates under the direction of the NATO Support and Procurement Organization (NSPO), which sets the strategic goals and policies for the agency. By centralizing and standardizing procurement and logistics services, the NSPA helps NATO members achieve cost savings, improved interoperability, and enhanced operational capability.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
