&lt;p&gt;The NSPA Information and Communication Technology (ICT) services are relying on&amp;nbsp;three underlying infrastructures:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Network&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Local Area Networks (LANs) to allow NSPA users to reachback ICT systems located in the NSPA datacenters.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Wide Area Networks (WANs) to allow NSPA remote offices and mobile users to securely reach back the NSPA datacenters located in Luxembourg&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Metropolitan Area Networks (MANs) to securely interconnect NSPA datacenters and Outside Cabling Plants (OCPs) located in Luxemourg.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Unified Communication (UC)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
